The paper deals with the problem of estimating the probability of an observed string drawn i.i.d. from an unknown distribution. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a novel sequence probability estimator, which could be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
